results.name: Expansion of Product_{i=0..m-1} (1 + x^(2*i+1)) for m=4.
comment: Product_{i=0..m-1} (1 + x^(2*i+1)) is the Poincaré polynomial for GL(m).
Number of self-conjugate partitions of n into at most 4 parts. Also, number of partitions of n into distinct odd parts not larger than 7. - _Álvar Ibeas_, Jul 30 2020
reference: H. Weyl, The Classical Groups, Princeton, 1946, see p. 233.
maple: f:=proc(m) local x,t1; t1:=mul((1+x^(2*i+1)),i=0..m-1); series(expand(t1),x,200); end;
xref: Cf. A169987-A169995 (these are all rows of the triangle in A178666), A000700.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Aug 29 2010
